column5: Joey,  You are our Sunshine Girl.  Right about beautiful women generally having low self esteem. No one is usually brave enough to approach a gorgeous woman and they think it's because they really aren't that pretty. A famous actress told me that years ago. That's how this mug ended up with a beautiful wife. Most importantly beautiful below all that smooth skin.  As for the woman in question, she gives big head, I mean has a big head. Couldn't help it, sorry.

dang, now my conscience is kickin me....in hindsight here, gotta give her/any girl props for having the confidence to share her body with the public to be drooled over/criticized....I was friends with a mildly successful model in college (paid promos, runway, print), she had severe self image issues and she was beautiful, like 11 out of 10...very sad stuff and I guess most guys won't ever understand that aspect  and like jedi mentioned, that pic is horrible, lighting and pose are both awkward...  but she should get bonus points for being into fishing

I'm with HeadHunter...that's not even real, hence one of the reasons it looks so unappealing. Some 'stock' body shot with what appears to be a Polaroid of one of The Sun office assistants with a ball cap on. Maybe the emodel market is drying up. And agreed...a 4th grader can use Photoshop better than that. Does the media really believe we're that gullible?

The Sun has always been 'creative' with their sunshine girls. I had a friend who was one once. Her blurb said she wanted to be a veterinarian and dreamed of going sky diving........ she hates animals and has a fear of heights.  After having a good laugh, she mentioned that they took a bunch of photos, paid her and asked her to leave. The blurbs are totally made up.
looks like misty's cafe material
